 Port Elizabeth - Bethelsdorp police, in Port Elizabeth, on Friday appealed to the public for any information relating to an incident where a 46-year-old man from Mallow Street, Ext 33, in Bethelsdorp, was found beaten to death. "It is alleged that at about 06:00, on Friday morning, a passer-by alerted police of a body lying in an open field between Ext 33 in Bethelsdorp and Kwanoxolo," described police spokesperson, W/OFF Alwin Labans. "Eugene Rossouw was last seen by his girlfriend on Thursday night, at about 20:00. "He sustained multiple head injuries. "Police suspect he may have been brutally assaulted." W/O Labans said that the reason for the fatal assault is yet to be established and suspects are unknown at this stage. "Anyone who can assist police in their investigation is asked to contact SAPS Bethelsdorp detectives on 041 4043046 or Crime Stop 08600 10111. All information supplied is strictly confidential and callers have the right to remain anonymous." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 